article.headline: North Dakota 27, Northwestern St. 20
article.story: NATCHITOCES, La. -- Ismael Bamba's third-quarter touchdown catch helped North Dakota beat Northwestern State 27-20 on Saturday night. Bamba caught six passes for 98 yards, including a 55-yard touchdown with 12 seconds remaining in the third quarter as North Dakota (1-1) built a 25-13 lead. North Dakota quarterback Landry was 12-of-20 for 156 yards and a touchdown. Mitch Sutton completed his only pass for a 17-yard touchdown to Ryan Dressler. Sutton also ran for 76 yards and a touchdown. Tyler Wolfe kept Northwestern State (0-3) in the game by completing 25-of-38 passes for 308 yards and three touchdowns. Wolfe threw a 9-yard touchdown pass to William Griffin with 1:35 remaining to cut North Dakota's lead to 25-20. After Northwestern State failed to convert an onside kick, North Dakota punted the ball to the 2-yard line and got a safety on the game's final play.
